<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language> en-US</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 15:28:17 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Threads adds a chronological feed as Twitter burns to the ground]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>随着 Meta 开始推出查看您关注的人按时间顺序发布的帖子的选项， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/threads/">Threads</a>将会变得更加有用。许多观察家表示，这是 Threads 真正与 Twitter 竞争所需的关键功能，Twitter 长期以来一直是实时信息的重要来源。但随着 Twitter（ <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-ceo-teases-banking-and-payment-plans-in-memo-about-x-rebrand-175218664.html">抱歉，X</a> ）所有者埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk) 继续将他的应用程序化为废墟，Threads 看起来像是一个更可行的获取最新新闻和更新的目的地。您需要更新到最新版本的 Threads 才能查看按时间顺序排列的提要，但由于这是逐步推出的，因此它可能不会立即显示给您。</p><p>马克·扎克伯格 (Mark Zuckerberg) 宣布在他的 Instagram 广播频道上推出按时间顺序排列的内容（Instagram 负责人亚当·莫塞里 (Adam Mosseri)<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.threads.net/@mosseri/post/CuYvSTItD5L">不久前表示</a>，这样的选项即将推出）。 Meta 首席执行官补充说，Threads 获得了另一个至关重要的功能，即翻译。扎克伯格表示，未来还会有更多功能， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/all-the-questions-we-still-have-about-threads-153059430.html">希望包括</a>从网络向 Threads 发帖的能力、直接消息、改进的可访问性、更好的搜索以及类似 TweetDeck 的方式来密切关注 Threads 帖子。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/threads-adds-a-chronological-feed-as-twitter-burns-to-the-ground-152817251.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/threads-adds-a-chronological-feed-as-twitter-burns-to-the-ground-152817251.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1e395551-4281-45dd-ad5a-7a06a850d624</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 25 Jul 2023 15:28:17 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690299008</ingested><modified> 2023-07-25T15:30:10+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="3840" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/e4dc9d60-1c57-11ee-aa61-d9a3c985eaeb" width="5760"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3840" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/e4dc9d60-1c57-11ee-aa61-d9a3c985eaeb" width="5760"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[La foto tomada en Nueva York el jueves 6 de julio de 2923 muestra la nueva aplicación de Meta, llamada Threads, creada para rivalizar con Twitter.(AP Foto/Richard Drew)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[META-TWITTER RIVALIDAD]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best gaming headsets for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>大多数时候，最好的游戏耳机根本不是“游戏耳机”。尽管这些设备通常被认为是更广泛的耳机市场中的独特利基市场，但它们最终<em>仍然是耳机</em>。虽然获得一款听起来不错的游戏耳机当然不是不可能的，但这样做的成本仍然比同类的有线耳机更高（是的，这些仍然存在）。</p><p>如果您希望在给定的价位上获得最细腻的声音，并且不需要特别便携的设备（无论您是在游戏机还是 PC 上玩游戏，通常都是这种情况），那么优质的有线耳机仍然是您的最佳选择。如果您需要与朋友聊天，您可以随时购买外置麦克风，无论是 USB 麦克风、更便宜的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-mobile-microphones-for-recording-with-a-phone-154536629.html">夹式麦克风</a>还是独立耳机麦克风（如<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://antlionaudio.com/collections/microphones/">Antlion ModMic</a>或<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAc3eyz3tAa5ZiXqoOSXXUJbQ9_Y1rClL-8LF-6d_J8BW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FV-MODA-BoomPro-Microphone-Gaming-Communication%2Fdp%2FB00BJ17WKK%2F">V-Moda BoomPro）</a> 。在许多情况下，这些将使您的声音听起来比游戏耳机附带的声音更清晰、更饱满。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>但我们确实认识到，许多人只是想要一种一体化组合的便利性，不管价值和美学如何。因此，在过去几个月测试了几十副之后，我们整理了一份适合游戏的优质耳机和专用游戏耳机的列表。我们建议您首先考虑前者，但所有这些都应该让您的游戏时间更加愉快。</p><h2>好的游戏耳机需要注意什么</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/7a99ecc0-d95c-11ed-b13c-943d83f982b8" alt="HyperX Cloud Stinger 2 是一款带有内置麦克风的黑色游戏耳机，放置在户外环境中的白色桌子上。" data-uuid="418ab01d-8853-3a4d-8a2e-10b7ce177a91"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Jeff Dunn / Engadget</div></figure><p>评估耳机是一项特别主观的工作，因此称一副耳机绝对是“最好的”是一件愚蠢的事。在某种程度上，无论您是否是发烧友，一切都变成了品味问题。对于大多数人来说，具有宽广声场和强大成像性能的耳机（即能够正确定位声音的能力，以便您可以更精确地辨别脚步声和其他游戏效果来自何处）将提供最身临其境的游戏体验，让您感觉自己的头部<em>处于给</em>定场景中。</p><p>为此，您需要一副采用开放式设计的高品质耳机。也就是说，耳罩式耳机的耳罩不能完全将耳朵与空气和外界噪音隔离。最大的代价是，这些本质上很糟糕，无法将您与外部声音隔离开来，并阻止其他人听到您正在演奏的内容。因此，如果你经常在嘈杂的环境中玩游戏，它们的好处就会减弱。但在安静的房间里，最好的开放式后背配对听起来比更常见的封闭式模型更宽广、更精确。</p><p>更多争论的是一款好的游戏耳机应该发出<em>怎样的</em>声音。如果您想要一款能够在竞技性多人游戏中有所帮助的耳机，您可能会更喜欢具有更平坦声音特征的耳机，这样游戏的混音就不会在一个方向上过度增强并掩盖您周围发生的事情的较小细节。稍微明亮一点的声音，稍微推动高频的声音，也可能有效。开放式耳机几乎不会有巨大的低音，因此您几乎不必担心低端声音会混淆其余的特征。从这个角度来看，绝大多数游戏耳机都是封闭式且重低音的，这一事实似乎有悖常理。</p><p>不过，很多人都喜欢贝斯。如果您不仅仅担心竞技比赛，一些额外的低端可以为重型动作场景或激动人心的配乐增添一丝兴奋感。您仍然不希望一副能够过度增强声音的耳机（许多专用游戏耳机就是这样做的），但关键是，使一副耳机对一个人来说“身临其境”的东西可能对另一个人来说听起来很乏味。</p><h2>最佳游戏耳机：拜亚动力 DT 900 Pro X </h2><p><core-commerce id="492a8e7747d84e979413f30261071c8d" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAftHZ3ObpyTnCGlnlk1QTt5XdsUA6Chr2_wDQQY2PZNc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09G777VG7%2F">拜亚动力 DT 900 Pro X</a>应该会令很多愿意为游戏而购买<em>优质</em>耳机的人感到满意。这对耳机具有出色的成像性能和开放式设计所期望的宽敞声场。与许多开放式耳机相比，这里的低音也更加明显。正如预期的那样，深沉的低音仍然没有太多，但有足够的温暖来给游戏中的爆炸声带来更多的动力，而不会使中频变得混乱。总体而言，中频是最受重视的，但它们很清晰，当您试图在<em>《反恐精英》</em>等竞技性 FPS 游戏中聆听敌方玩家的声音时，这种前瞻性并不是一件坏事。高音没有那么用力，但既不过度凹陷也不刺耳。</p><p>所有这些都意味着 DT 900 Pro X 听起来细致但不乏味，因此无论您是想赢得多人游戏还是享受更具电影感的单人游戏体验，它都应该表现良好。当您不玩游戏时，您也能听到令人愉悦的音乐声。</p><p>一切都构建得很好。如果您的头部较大，它的夹紧力会比一般耳机稍重，​​但它可以很好地平衡重量，而且其极其柔软的丝绒耳垫有助于在长时间佩戴时保持舒适。它配备了两根可拆卸的电缆，其中包括一根三米长的电缆，如果您坐得离电脑较远，则非常方便。不过，这种设计不能折叠。</p><p>与所有开放式耳机一样，DT 900 Pro X 会泄漏游戏音频并产生大量噪音，因此在旅途中使用效果不佳。显然，如果您有能力升级到像<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5zZW5uaGVpc2VyLWhlYXJpbmcuY29tL2VuLVVTL3AvaGQtODAwLXMvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNmZhNjdhNy03NmE4LTRlZjEtOWM4ZC01OWM0NjNjYjNhZGIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAa6x7Onjo7WKOjzbCSxIVnseZmZkmCiglwJ606VhetVN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sennheiser-hearing.com%2Fen-US%2Fp%2Fhd-800-s%2F">Sennheiser HD 800 S</a>这样的超高端耳机，您将获得更多的空间和逼真的细节。但对于相对实惠的 250 至 300 美元来说，DT 900 Pro X 应该可以满足。</p><h2> 200 美元以下的最佳游戏耳机：Sennheiser HD 560S </h2><p><core-commerce id="fe20463957704cd4855a0e6658ed6270" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您不想花那么多钱， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWDyYK2qqowd_jCmxamL_U0xsNiUmfFzxSo8Rr1ule3g&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB08J9MVB6W%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1%3Fsmid%3DATVPDKIKX0DER%26psc%3D1">Sennheiser HD 560S</a>是另一款出色的开放式耳机，售价通常在 150 美元左右。与 DT 900 Pro X 一样，它具有宽广的声场，可帮助您沉浸在特定游戏中。总体而言，它的声音稍微更加中性，因此您不会觉得错过了混音的任何部分，并且它从高音和中频中检索了大量的细节。不过，低音爆发力较小，而高音虽然较多，但有时听起来可能很刺耳。成像也没有<em>那么</em>细致，但也算不上差。</p><p>从设计角度来看，HD 560S 长时间佩戴非常舒适。它们不会对那些大头的人（像您真正的那样）施加太大的压力，而且丝绒耳垫会轻轻地包裹您的耳朵。附带的电缆也是可拆卸的。然而，塑料框架感觉不像 DT 900 Pro X 那样坚固或优质，因此您不会想随意地将它们扔来扔去。它也不会阻挡太多外界噪音，也不会阻止您周围的人听到您正在演奏的内容。尽管如此，HD 560S 仍然令人愉悦且物超所值。</p><h2> 50 美元以下的最佳游戏耳机：Koss KSC75 </h2><p><core-commerce id="fd9ce75cc4834016bb34789626bb1099" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果你的花费不能超过 50 美元，那么<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/koss-ksc75-headphones-irl-143533671.html">仍然很难</a>超越<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQfD8I5u9Wr_HH3Mk133wyEZwLmX6ZZSO7f1nbXbLB5n&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FKoss-KSC75-Portable-Stereophone-Headphones%2Fdp%2FB0006B486K%3Fth%3D1">Koss KSC75</a> 。它的售价为 20 美元，但纯粹从音质来看，它比一些价格接近 100 美元的耳机要好。这对耳机显然缺乏深沉的低音，因此您无法从游戏中的效果中获得浓郁的<em>魅力</em>。您也不会听到使用上面价格较高的耳机所听到的所有复杂细节。但它对声音的定位准确，其开放式设计赋予了它真正的宽度感。这对于竞技游戏来说具有极高的价值。</p><p>问题是它的构造就像一套免费的航空耳机。 KSC75 采用奇怪的夹式设计，虽然重量轻，但并不适合每个人。它看起来确实要花 20 美元，尽管 Koss 为其提供<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2tvc3MuY29tL3BhZ2VzL3dhcnJhbnR5LXJlcGFpciIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTZmYTY3YTctNzZhOC00ZWYxLTljOGQtNTljNDYzY2IzYWRiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATq3XDDgE-dSvLRyTZM88jDPxijB4fPBTFoX-Vj8QyK1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fkoss.com%2Fpages%2Fwarranty-repair">终身保修</a>，基本上可以让你以每件 9 美元的价格获得无限的替换品。即使 KSC75 已经有 20 年历史了，它的声音仍然相对均衡，特别适合游戏。</p><h2>最佳游戏耳机：Astro A40 TR </h2><p><core-commerce id="c990c3baa2b143c2a225d3fd9dced20b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您必须拥有带有内置麦克风的专用游戏耳机，请考虑<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDdOU1JZREg5P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLXNtLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNmZhNjdhNy03NmE4LTRlZjEtOWM4ZC01OWM0NjNjYjNhZGIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAevIZTvveh8dqiw9CG4f9NRCLh028Al8JIaATGwTlTA3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07NSRYDH9">Astro A40 TR</a> 。另一对开放式耳机，它的声场比同类产品中的普通耳机更宽敞——尽管它无法与更好的非游戏耳机相提并论——而且它通常可以正确定位声音。这种配置强调低音，让爆炸声产生平滑而令人满意的重击声，但它并没有像许多其他面向游戏的耳机那样过度。</p><p>这里的声音仍然落后于 DT 900 Pro X 或 HD 560S，特别是对于在线射击玩家来说，因为推高的低音和中低音可能会进一步削弱更精细的细节。脚步声通常听起来不那么清晰。但与大多数游戏耳机相比，A40 的轮廓更加平衡，能够很好地让您沉浸在繁忙场景的声音中。</p><p>舒适度也不应该成为问题。 A40 的体积较大，但重量分布均匀，不会压得太紧。毛茸茸的耳垫柔软透气，耳罩足够宽敞，适合较大的耳朵。不过，这款耳机具有常见的开放式缺点：它会泄漏大量声音，并且几乎零外界噪音。该设计看起来也很“游戏玩家”，而且没有内置音量控制。整个东西主要由塑料制成，尽管它看起来并不那么脆弱。</p><p>与此同时，A40 的麦克风也还不错。当您聊天时，它会拾取背景噪音，并且声音听起来有些低沉。它很实用，但你购买 A40 首先是因为它的音质。麦克风也不可拆卸，但您可以轻松地将其向上翻转并移开。</p><p> A40 已经问世四年了，但其价格已从 150 美元降至更合理的 130 美元。 Astro 以 130 美元的价格出售带有额外控制的可选<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-best-dac-for-lossless-high-resolution-music-iphone-android-160056147.html">DAC</a> ，但以这个价格，我们强烈建议购买一个好的“普通”耳机和外部麦克风。</p><h2>最佳预算游戏耳机：HyperX Cloud Stinger 2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="ff3b0030a2cf43c984a48388b03a114b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>您找不到低于 50 美元的优质开放式游戏耳机，因此，如果您预算紧张且需要内置麦克风，则必须在音质上做出妥协。考虑到这一点， <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfh2E5Ka9uLQvooXb479JP4pK_Z0_40HFg_nNxE4Yv0q&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHyperX-Cloud-Stinger-Swivel-Mute%2Fdp%2FB0B8PGDMWK%2F">HyperX Cloud Stinger 2</a>的典型市场价格为 40 美元，是一个不错的选择。它的麦克风掩盖了其低廉的价格，使声音听起来相对清晰和准确。事实上，这是 Astro A40 的明显进步。它不可拆卸，但很灵活，当您将其滑开时，它会自动静音。这对耳机的舒适度也很不错，因为仿皮耳罩不会紧紧夹住，并且在重要的地方有足够的柔软填充物。</p><p> Cloud Stinger 2 具有 V 形声音轮廓，也就是说，它夸大了低音和高音，同时削弱了中音。就其本身而言还不错，而且肯定会给动作场面带来沉重的冲击感。但上低音被推到了随着时间的推移可能会感到疲劳的程度，并且你会失去一些在听起来更自然的耳机上听到的精细细节。由于这是一款廉价的封闭式耳机，Cloud Stinger 2 听起来也不像上面的耳机那样宽广，而且在准确定位声音方面也没有那么细致入微。因此，它对于竞技游戏来说不太理想，尽管它与许多其他游戏一起听起来仍然“有趣”。</p><p>除此之外，其制作质量和塑料设计感觉很便宜，尽管它是封闭式的，但它并不能阻挡太多外部噪音，而且它的电缆不可拆卸。尽管如此，你必须在这个价格范围内选择你的战斗。 Cloud Stinger 2 有缺陷，但它的表现足够好，足以成为特定类型人群的好耳机。</p><h2>关于无线游戏耳机的快速 PSA</h2><p>大多数人不需要无线游戏耳机。 PS5 和 Xbox Series X/S 游戏机的控制器中内置有耳机插孔，并且在 Nintendo Switch 和大多数游戏 PC 上仍然可以使用。合格的无线型号的成本通常高于同类有线游戏耳机的成本，并且在无线版本上，您通常会得到更差的音频质量和不太清晰的麦克风。您还可能面临引入延迟问题的风险。后者就是为什么非游戏蓝牙耳机在这里不可行的原因。</p><h2>最佳无线游戏耳机：HyperX Cloud Alpha Wireless </h2><p><core-commerce id="faca9b77d22448678e03a68527b173df" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您<em>确实</em>想要一款无线耳机（例如，如果您的游戏电脑位于办公桌的远端），您应该寻找一副能够让“无线”部分不那么明显的耳机。 <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9IeXBlclgtQ2xvdWQtQWxwaGEtV2lyZWxlc3MtTm9pc2UtY2FuY2VsaW5nL2RwL0IwOVRSVzU3V0I_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1zbS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTZmYTY3YTctNzZhOC00ZWYxLTljOGQtNTljNDYzY2IzYWRiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAXiIf4kCOaA9SHR2qrbtxdd-cU-3s2WpTGOwd5lezaNS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHyperX-Cloud-Alpha-Wireless-Noise-canceling%2Fdp%2FB09TRW57WB%3Fth%3D1">HyperX Cloud Alpha Wireless</a>能够做到这一点要归功于其超长的电池寿命。 HyperX 将其额定为 300 小时，但我们能够以中等容量再挤出几十个小时。如果你好奇这是如何实现的，iFixit 做了一个<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:YouTube;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=89f68c82-f255-44fa-8db9-03fec996b93a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=YouTube&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4OWY2OGM4Mi1mMjU1LTQ0ZmEtOGRiOS0wM2ZlYzk5NmI5M2EiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj01dDBKeXpoMHZlbyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTZmYTY3YTctNzZhOC00ZWYxLTljOGQtNTljNDYzY2IzYWRiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAcVsOdohnTocKXz7QzdduiByIInEsqXY_W1NBWb3suhG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D5t0Jyzh0veo">有用的拆解</a>，但可以毫不夸张地说，一次充电可以让你玩<em>几个月</em>。</p><p>这里的声音是许多游戏耳机的典型声音：略呈 V 形，低音过分强调，可以使游戏效果听起来令人兴奋，但通常会呈现脚步声和更精细的细节，但清晰度较差。作为一款封闭式耳机，它听起来也不像上面的开放式耳机那样宽敞或自然。 （采用开放式设计的无线游戏耳机实际上是不存在的。）按照无线游戏耳机的标准，这还不错，而且它通常将声音放置在正确的位置；它只是没有像 Astro A40 这样的产品那样进行优化调整或设计。</p><p>耳机本身一次佩戴几个小时都很舒适，毛绒衬垫不会感觉太紧，但耳垫上的人造皮革材料可能会让你的耳朵感觉有点温暖。一切都很坚固，头带也很灵活。吊杆麦克风也很好，尽管这是相对于其他无线耳机而言的。它可以很好地消除背景噪音并保持声音清晰，但听起来不像带有良好麦克风的有线耳机那样清晰或饱满。不过比A40好一些。</p><p>警告：不要为 HyperX 的配套软件烦恼。虽然您可以使用该公司的<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://hyperx.com/pages/ngenuity">Ngenuity</a>应用程序自定义耳机的 EQ 并激活<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://dts.com/dts-headphonex/">DTS:X</a>环绕声功能，但<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/HyperX/comments/uaiapq/hyperx_cloud_alpha_wireless_latency/">一些用户</a>报告说这会带来明显的延迟，而 HyperX <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://xander51.medium.com/hyperxs-hilarious-fix-for-their-headset-driver-latency-issues-e80f39b9faff">似乎并没有</a>修复它。如果您确实需要这些功能，请使用第三方 EQ 应用程序以及<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Microsoft;elmt:;cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=67071605-d4df-494e-8d9c-c9c236b8bb38&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Microsoft&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAejkZw8zPCdWffud4pYxus0GvAzcoxSD9FUgKS7c626q&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fwindows%2Fhow-to-turn-on-spatial-sound-in-windows-10-ca2700a0-6519-448d-5434-56f499d59c96" class="rapid-with-clickid">Windows</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:PlayStation;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0f845666-5cc0-42c7-863d-d873ae1b6087&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=PlayStation&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATLUYwciozEtfsV856Spv7YocFk_kLsQObdfPNVDZviP&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fsupport%2Fhardware%2F3d-audio-ps5%2F">PS5</a>中内置的空间音频工具。默认情况下，随附的 USB 适配器提供稳定的无线连接。</p><p>另一个需要注意的是，Cloud Alpha Wireless 仅适用于 PC 和 PlayStation 游戏机，或对接时的 Switch。它也无法通过电缆或蓝牙进行连接。如果您正在寻找 Xbox 的合适替代品，我们在下面列出了一些建议。</p><h2>最佳优质无线游戏耳机：Audeze Maxwell </h2><p><core-commerce id="7af406b256fa49fe94800a5d12f75950" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hdWRlemUuY29tL3Byb2R1Y3RzL21heHdlbGwtd2lyZWxlc3MtZ2FtaW5nLWhlYWRzZXQ_dmFyaWFudD00MDA5NDc2NTAyMzMxMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTZmYTY3YTctNzZhOC00ZWYxLTljOGQtNTljNDYzY2IzYWRiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAZrjFKRcjut7EJ7RSJsEr372lU_LWDvK9iOfygaatKXG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.audeze.com%2Fproducts%2Fmaxwell-wireless-gaming-headset%3Fvariant%3D40094765023310">Audeze Maxwell 的</a>售价为 299 美元（Xbox 型号为 329 美元），价格并不惊人，但如果您有足够的现金可以烧，它是一款具有真正令人印象深刻的声音和麦克风质量的无线耳机。它的<a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.howtogeek.com/327846/what-are-planar-magnetic-headphones/">平面磁性</a>驱动器可以很好地再现给定场景中较小的复杂性，并且其默认签名就像常见“游戏耳机”声音的更精致版本。低音流畅、有冲击力但不臃肿，高音清脆但不过分尖锐。中频的一些效果听起来很薄，因为这是一个<em>&nbsp;</em>封闭式耳机，无法提供与上述开放式型号相同的沉浸式宽度和精确成像。具有讽刺意味的是，它可能比游戏更适合音乐。尽管如此，对于一款无线耳机来说，它还是异常令人愉悦和细致的。 Audeze 的应用程序还包括多个 EQ 预设。</p><p>同样，Maxwell 的可拆卸吊杆麦克风也很出色。它在消除背景噪音方面表现出色，虽然声音失去了一些空气感，但听起来仍然比我们测试过的大多数无线耳机更清晰、更饱满。</p><p> Maxwell 体积较大，其头带采用了一种奇怪的悬挂机制，如果不取下耳机就无法进行有效调节。柔软的软垫耳罩可能会让您的耳朵感觉温暖，但它们可以使耳机保持舒适并隔离相当多的外部噪音。高端设计也给人一种厚重的感觉，头带由钢制成。基本控件内置于左耳罩中，除了 USB-C 无线适配器外，该设备还可以通过蓝牙或 3.5 毫米电缆进行连接。您甚至可以同时与两台设备配对，一台通过适配器，另一台通过蓝牙。然而，耳机需要开机才能通过电缆播放音乐。</p><p> Audeze 将 Maxwell 的电池续航时间评为大约 80 小时，但如果你以高音量播放或大量使用蓝牙或侧音等功能，电池续航时间就会缩短。虽然这无法与 Cloud Alpha Wireless 相比，但它仍然比大多数无线耳机要好得多。</p><h2>其他著名的游戏耳机</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/13435120-d960-11ed-bc67-dccf7cbeb8df" alt="罗技的 G535 无线游戏耳机放置在户外露台的藤椅上。" data-uuid="25e87b51-9777-3360-90f6-ffb5209fec3f"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Jeff Dunn / Engadget</div></figure><h3>赛睿 Arctis Nova Pro </h3><p><core-commerce id="23aec4369e544402957e78b291f07fca" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATBDtCTmrhfdzRxzkwm41CS0WjvaetVcz3ro1ne9GIG1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09ZW52XSQ%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1%3Fsmid%3DATVPDKIKX0DER%26psc%3D1">SteelSeries Arctis Nova Pro</a>的价格过高，为 250 美元，它可以使高频听起来刺耳，但它的低音和中音很好，超级舒适，而且其可伸缩麦克风明显比 Astro A40 更清晰。其附带的 DAC 也很有用，可让您调整耳机的 EQ 和游戏/聊天组合。不过，虽然封闭式设计在阻挡外界噪音方面稍微好一些，但它无法提供与 A40 相同的宽度感。</p><h3> SteelSeries Arctis Nova Pro 无线</h3><p><core-commerce id="e74e0e79d07c4f4796db3f1d7c39d784" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> SteelSeries 还销售 Nova Pro 的<a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXCIfWug_-E2M4ZAJ3XP0zoGba2bLRCUolTIs0PD9Iyy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09ZWKD9TF%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1%3Fsmid%3DATVPDKIKX0DER%26th%3D1">无线版本</a>，其零售价通常在 300 至 350 美元之间。 Audeze Maxwell 对大多数人来说听起来会更好，但这可能是其最接近的竞争对手，并且它具有有用的额外功能，例如同时连接到多个游戏设备（使用 Xbox 型号）和热插拔电池组的能力。</p><h3>赛睿 Arctis Nova 7X </h3><p><core-commerce id="720e3077f4aa48c89988b8a6dae06307" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您需要 Xbox 的 Cloud Alpha Wireless 的无线替代品， <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TdGVlbFNlcmllcy1BcmN0aXMtTXVsdGktUGxhdGZvcm0tR2FtaW5nLU1vYmlsZS1IZWFkc2V0L2RwL0IwQjhRUDVCR0Q_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tc20tMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImE2ZmE2N2E3LTc2YTgtNGVmMS05YzhkLTU5YzQ2M2NiM2FkYiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASgMqXN8q3hSHiaKMV0Az_U8S1ROhV-Eajl4Wcb1expQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSteelSeries-Arctis-Multi-Platform-Gaming-Mobile-Headset%2Fdp%2FB0B8QP5BGD">SteelSeries Arctis Nova 7X</a>应该可以。这是另一对低音前置麦克风，其麦克风与 Cloud Alpha Wireless 上的麦克风相当。与其他 Nova 型号一样，它提供多种连接选项，包括蓝牙和 3.5 毫米电缆。虽然它是针对 Xbox 销售的，但它也可以连接到 PC 和 PS5。不过，它的 30 小时左右的电池续航时间远远低于 Cloud Alpha Wireless，而且它的声音特征可能会让高音听起来有些不稳定。</p><h3> HyperX Cloud Alpha 版</h3><p><core-commerce id="06d2323c6ff24304ac758462dc846880" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>有线<a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDc0TkJTRjlOP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLXNtLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNmZhNjdhNy03NmE4LTRlZjEtOWM4ZC01OWM0NjNjYjNhZGIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZBXk5cw9Z-Zz-xHLFBiaCe1h-9KKpmO19dQ6jLR-Z-I&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB074NBSF9N">HyperX Cloud Alpha 的</a>售价通常为 80 美元或更低，如果您确实需要一款封闭式游戏耳机，那么以这个价格来看，它是 Cloud Stinger 2 和 Astro A40 之间不错的中间价格。它很旧，但它的毛绒耳垫和头带仍然很舒适，它的可拆卸麦克风虽然不是很好，但仍然比 Astro 的麦克风好。然而，它的高音没有被充分强调，而且它听起来比 A40 更“在你的脑海中”。</p><h3>罗技 G535 </h3><p><core-commerce id="225a6214d5094994ab0a29c0d980fff4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQnLpIUEvZCzFdDxJcN1GnzPdiQ-wJH7JtjAG1SEiR7c&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLogitech-Lightweight-Wireless-Gaming-Headset%2Fdp%2FB08KY2WFGP%3Fth%3D1">罗技 G535</a>是一款令人印象深刻的轻巧（236 克）且舒适的无线耳机，售价通常为 100 美元。与 Cloud Alpha Wireless 和 Arctis Nova 7X 相比，它具有更中性的声音特征：不平坦，但不太受大而重低音的影响。它可以使中频细节听起来很薄，如果有的话，它可以使用更多<em>的</em>低音，但总体而言这是一种令人愉快的聆听体验。它还可以通过蓝牙连接。然而，与 Cloud Alpha Wireless（已经算不上出色）相比，它的麦克风失去了一些饱满度，而且其 30 小时左右的电池续航时间也大幅下降。另外，它不能与 Xbox 配合使用，而且奇怪的是它会迫使你将音量调到可听的水平。但如果您不想在无线耳机上花费太多，那么它是我们测试过的 100 美元及以下选项中最好的。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-headset-130006477.html?src=rss]]>;</description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-headset-130006477.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a6fa67a7-76a8-4ef1-9c8d-59c463cb3adb</guid><dc:creator>杰夫·邓恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 25 Jul 2023 15:05:57 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690297870</ingested><modified> 2023-07-25T15:11:22+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jeff Dunn]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/a05a6150-d967-11ed-bc5f-50bcb25e8639" width="1799"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/a05a6150-d967-11ed-bc5f-50bcb25e8639" width="1799"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Jeff Dunn / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Best gaming headsets]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Best gaming headsets]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[GM says a next-gen Chevy Bolt is on the way]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/gm/"><ins>通用汽车公司</ins></a>对<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/chevy-bolt/"><ins>雪佛兰 Bolt 的</ins></a>开发还没有结束。早在 4 月份，就有消息称该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-will-stop-making-the-chevy-bolt-ev-and-euv-later-this-year-160540118.html"><ins>将在今年停止生产</ins></a>流行的、经济实惠的 EV 和<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chevrolet-bolt-euv-review-video-160016098.html"><ins>EUV</ins></a> ，这主要是因为它依赖于旧的电池技术，而且制造它的工厂正在进行改造。然而，对于电动汽车的粉丝来说，有一些积极的消息，因为通用汽车已<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://media.chevrolet.com/media/us/en/chevrolet/home.detail.html/content/Pages/news/us/en/2023/jul/0725-chevrolet.html"><ins>确认</ins></a>新版本的 Bolt 即将推出。</p><p>该公司尚未透露有关新款 Bolt 的更多细节——你需要等到今年晚些时候才能知道。不过，毫不奇怪，下一代车型将使用通用汽车的<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-is-placing-all-of-its-ev-eggs-in-the-ultum-battery-basket-163038784.html"><ins>Ultium 电池系统</ins></a>及其 Ultifi 软件平台。该公司表示，通过利用这些技术，它将能够“加速”将 Bolt 重新推向市场，但没有透露具体时间。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>通用汽车在<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://investor.gm.com/news-releases/news-release-details/gm-releases-2023-second-quarter-results-and-raises-full-year"><ins>季度财报电话会议</ins></a>上宣布了博尔特的消息。该公司表示，Bolt EV 和 EUV 销量将在 2023 年上半年达到迄今为止最强劲的水平。该公司公布的季度收入为 447 亿美元，同比增长 25%，但指出与 LG 的新合作伙伴关系产生了 7.92 亿美元的费用。通用汽车表示：“这项指控反映了通用汽车在<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-expands-fire-risk-recall-all-chevy-bolt-115934063.html"><ins>雪佛兰 Bolt EV 和 Bolt EUV 召回</ins></a>期间做出的有意识的决定，以超越传统补救措施的方式为客户提供服务。”</p><p>该公司于 2023 年前六个月在北美生产了约 50,000 辆电动汽车。下半年该目标将增加一倍。它的目标是到 2025 年在非洲大陆实现 100 万辆电动汽车的产能。</p><p>与此同时，雪佛兰今年还将推出另外三款电动汽车： <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chevrolet-silverado-ev-details-ces-debut-171551300.html"><ins>Silverado</ins></a> 、 <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-2024-chevrolet-blazer-ev-ss-rs-023052241.html"><ins>Blazer</ins></a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chevy-blazer-equinox-ev-teaser-184112130.html"><ins>Equinox</ins></a> 。该品牌将于<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cadillac-teases-the-electric-escalade-iq-ahead-of-an-august-9th-reveal-140045265.html"><ins>8 月 9 日</ins></a>发布其首款全尺寸电动 SUV Escalade IQ。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/gm-says-a-next-gen-chevy-bolt-is-on-the-way-144518735.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/gm-says-a-next-gen-chevy-bolt-is-on-the-way-144518735.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> cbfa924a-06e7-4838-aef9-3e0281e6772f</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 25 Jul 2023 14:45:18 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690295665</ingested><modified> 2023-07-25T14:34:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Athletics, Track & Field]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="800" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-11/20d1c600-26ca-11eb-abd7-c41845eff043" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="800" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-11/20d1c600-26ca-11eb-abd7-c41845eff043" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Roberto Baldwin/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[GM's Chevy Bolt EV]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[GM's Chevy Bolt EV]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Arc personalized web browser is now available to everyone]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>如果您想自定义（或<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-arc-internet-browser-lets-you-customize-or-vandalize-any-website-130010555.html">简单地破坏</a>）您访问的网站，那么您现在可以轻松完成。 The Browser Company 已<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://arc.net/">发布</a>适用于 Mac 的 Arc 1.0 浏览器，无需等待。完成的版本包括最近几周出现的一些功能，包括可选工具栏、网站“控制中心”以及对 Google Meet 视频通话的画中画支持。该软件也应该比以前的版本更精简、更快。</p><p>和以前一样，Arc 重新思考了 Web 浏览器的一些基础知识。您可以使用 Boost 来个性化网站的外观和布局，让您可以更改颜色、替换字体，甚至“切换”您不想看到的部分。虽然这并不适用于每个网站，但您可以与其他用户共享许多自定义设置。您可以使用编码和脚本来创建增强，但它们不需要这些专业知识。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>标签仍然存在。然而，您主要围绕可切换的虚拟空间（有效的选项卡组）组织浏览，以帮助您专注于给定的任务，例如工作或社交媒体追赶。您可以固定经常使用的网站，并且有一个命令栏可以吸引高级用户。</p><p>该公司表示，Arc 的 Windows 版本“即将推出”。如果您是 Chrome、Edge 或 Safari 浏览器的粉丝，这可能不会取代这些浏览器。它们仍然很好地涵盖了常见任务，并且熟悉的界面可能就足够了。然而，如果您希望能够根据自己的喜好重塑网络，那么 Arc 可能就是您所需要的。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-arc-personalized-web-browser-is-now-available-to-everyone-140015020.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-arc-personalized-web-browser-is-now-available-to-everyone-140015020.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ecef1b6e-58ad-4186-8c7e-661bdf06b405</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 25 Jul 2023 14:00:15 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690293015</ingested><modified> 2023-07-25T13:50:17+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1228" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/e7f3ff40-2aec-11ee-afd1-49b6589258c8" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1228" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/e7f3ff40-2aec-11ee-afd1-49b6589258c8" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[The Browser Company]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Arc browser customized version of Engadget website]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Arc browser customized version of Engadget website]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[DJI Air 3 review: A high-quality zoom adds new creative options]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> DJI 是最具创新性的小工具公司之一，不断用无人机尝试新事物，例如<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/djis-mavic-3-pro-comes-with-a-triple-camera-setup-130001265.html">Mavic 3 Pro</a>上的三摄像头设置。随着中型<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ESkktQ29udHJvbGxlci1XaWRlLUFuZ2xlLVByaW1hcnktQmF0dGVyaWVzL2RwL0IwQzdHVDE3TDM_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMXI0LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlZjIwNGRjNi0yYjY1LTQ5OGQtOGZkYS01NmIzNjhkMTU2NGEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdedJq4NygFK2g_WUvVSuiWQ5gnR9JzhxP7jYoVXmWzD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDJI-Controller-Wide-Angle-Primary-Batteries%2Fdp%2FB0C7GT17L3" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/DJI-Controller-Wide-Angle-Primary-Batteries/dp/B0C7GT17L3?ref_=ast_sto_dp&amp;th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Air 3摄像无人机</a>的推出，该公司推出了一种称为双主摄像头的新技巧。这意味着长焦相机与主相机具有相同的规格，而不是像<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dji-mavic-3-update-hands-on-video-141505594.html">Mavic 3</a>那样质量较差。这为飞行员开辟了新的可能性，为他们提供了两种创建电影镜头的方法。</p><p>与<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dji-air-2s-camera-drone-130053973.html">Air 2</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dji-air-2s-camera-drone-130053973.html">Air 2S</a>相比，它还有许多改进。它采用了大疆创新的O4传输系统，大大增加了航程，同时首次为Air无人机带来了Waypoint功能。它还大大延长了电池寿命，并且更加安静。除此之外，它的功能与 Mavic 3 Pro 的功能相当，具有全方位障碍物检测、焦点跟踪、延时摄影等功能。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="90607067caac463da9733834b88aa201" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>然而，与 Air 2S 上的 1 英寸传感器相比，一些买家可能会认为 1/1.3 英寸传感器是降级产品。它与 Mavic 3 Pro 和<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dji-mini-3-pro-review-130041928.html">Mini 3 Pro</a>型号相比如何？我和我的无人机飞行员朋友带着它在法国卢瓦尔河谷飞行来找出答案。</p><h3>设计与性能</h3><div id="9e12f20d9e454501997421c517b90560"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/IotwTU-Ojsk" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p> Air 3（名称不再是“Mavic”）采用前置双摄像头模块和类似的设计，看起来比 Air 2 和 Air 2S 更像 Mavic 3。它具有与 Mavic 3 相同的青蛙设计，并且可以像 Mavic 3 一样折叠起来，折叠成紧凑的尺寸以方便旅行。车身各处均设有全方位传感器，用于检测障碍物。存储方面，它配备了常见的 microSD 存储插槽，内部有 8GB 容量，仅供紧急使用。它也比 Air 2S 重很多，从 595 克增至 720 克。</p><p>同时，它借鉴了 Mini 3 Pro 的一些空气动力学技巧，特别是较大的螺旋桨，可将噪音降低至 81 分贝，使得在 100 英尺左右的高度飞行时几乎听不到声音。机身也更符合空气动力学原理，与过去的型号相比，向前飞行的范围更大，并且能够应对更强的风。</p><p>大部分额外重量来自新的 4,241 mAh 电池，比整个 Mini 3 Pro 重 267 克。它们的电池容量接近 Mavic 3 Pro 的电池容量，将 Air 3 的续航时间从 Air 2S 的 34 分钟大幅提升至 46 分钟。</p><p>在实际使用中，我们发现返航警告响起之前的飞行时间约为 35 分钟，具体取决于飞行方式和风向。这通常允许我们用三块充满电的电池飞行一整天。 DJI 还通过更新的电池集线器推出了新的充电功能，只需按一下按钮即可将电量从两块电量较弱的电池转移到电量最多的一块。如果您所在的位置无法充电，这样做可以让您享受更长的飞行时间。高容量电池的一个缺点是充电速度相对较慢。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/0eda9170-2a41-11ee-bb9b-8ec76c8eaa88" style="height:1238px;width:2200px;" alt="DJI Air 3评测：高品质变焦增添新创意选择" data-uuid="8176eef5-8300-353e-a397-30ce480e8971"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">史蒂夫·登特 (Steve Dent)</div></figure><p>另一个关键功能是下一代 O4 视频传输系统，可将传输范围从 15 公里增加到 20 公里（9.3 英里到 12.4 英里）。无人机的射程在欧洲可能是一个大问题，因为与美国相比，法律大大降低了传输功率。为了弥补这一点，DJI 在欧洲增加了一个新的 5.1GHz 频率，从我们在法国的测试中看到的情况来看，这似乎对棘手地形中的范围和传输丢包产生了很大影响。</p><p>在操控性和速度方面，Air 3很好地平衡了Mavic 3 Pro的稳定性和Mini 3 Pro的敏捷性。后者非常适合跟踪山地自行车和车辆等快速移动的物体，但它在强风中也能保持稳定。与此同时，如果拍摄对象在树林中移动，APAS 5.0 的避障能力非常出色，由于配备了额外的传感器，碰撞风险比 Mini 3 Pro 更低——尤其是侧面和后面的传感器。</p><p> Air 3 上提供了 DJI 的所有主要功能，例如 Active Track、Master Shots、Quickshots 和 Timelapse，并且适用于两款相机。主动跟踪用于锁定和跟踪拍摄对象，在两台相机上的工作原理大致相同。与大疆的其他无人机一样，它通常很可靠，但如果你在树林中追赶山地自行车手，它可能会有点滞后，并且跟踪可能会在没有警告的情况下关闭。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/0f16d720-2a41-11ee-bfff-a18bab6db8e9" style="height:1238px;width:2200px;" alt="DJI Air 3评测：高品质变焦增添新创意选择" data-uuid="a94d6687-0c77-390b-80eb-5bc8ecc6ba6a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">史蒂夫·登特 (Steve Dent)</div></figure><p>像 Dronie 和 Rocket 这样的 Quickshots 功能在添加长焦摄像头后变得更加有趣，可以增加额外的亲密感和戏剧性。障碍物检测在那里也很方便。因为一旦你点击“开始”，无人机就会自动飞行，所以很容易误判边界，所以最好知道如果它离某物太近它就会中止。</p><p>除了这些飞行模式之外，大疆创新还首次将Mavic 3的航点飞行模式引入到Air系列中。它可以让您提前计划飞行和相机移动，让您可以精确地重复一次飞行以进行多次拍摄、延时拍摄视频等。它需要一些时间来学习和设置，但它可以提供一致的结果。它还开辟了创造性的可能性，比如在白天和晚上进行延时摄影，然后将它们无缝地融合在一起。</p><p>除了Air 3之外，大疆还推出了新款RC-2，这是大疆继RC和RC Pro之后的第三款屏幕控制器。这是两者之间的一个很好的折衷方案，因为它比 1,200 美元的 RC Pro 便宜得多。同时，它比RC拥有更亮的屏幕、更厚重的手感、更精准的操控。它可以单独购买，也可以与 Air 3 Fly More 套件捆绑销售。 DJI 还发布了另一款新控制器 RC-N2，实际上是 RC-N1 的更新，主要优点是新的 O4 传输系统。</p><h3>相机</h3><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="e8565308-bf87-4774-8631-872fd3e4bc57" /><p>Air 3 的重要理念是两个摄像头的质量相同。因此，它配备了 1/1.3 英寸 24mm（相当于 35mm）f/1.7 主摄像头和 70mm f/2.8 长焦摄像头。这些焦距与 Mavic 3 Pro 上的两个主摄像头相匹配，传感器尺寸与 Mini 3 Pro 和 Mavic 3 Pro 上的长焦摄像头相同。</p><p> 70 毫米镜头特别适合拍摄动作或英雄镜头，增添刺激感和更自然的视角。例如，它具有完美的人像焦距，非常适合在婚礼上拍摄人物照片。 It also lets you stay a greater distance from subjects for safety or other reasons, while compressing the space between them. As usual, the main wide camera can be used for establishing, overhead, follow and other shots. And with identical sensors, it&#39;s easy to match footage from the two cameras while editing.</p><p> The sensors have dual native ISO support for improved light sensitivity, and deliver 4K 60p in HDR or 4K at up to 100 fps with slo-mo only playback. 1080p can be shot at 200 fps with slo-mo playback as well. The camera module can be tilted down 90 degrees and up 60, and it&#39;s the first Air series drone supporting 2.7K vertical 9:16 video. </p><section data-eng-breakout="70742212b09c4176940d3aa6f0c13d1a" data-eng-breakout-type="e2ehero"><img class="e2ehero-url" src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3dc25c90-2a67-11ee-b4ff-8db71235397d" style="height:1238px;width:2200px;" alt="DJI Air 3评测：高品质变焦增添新创意选择"></section><p> Both cameras support 10-bit 4:2:0 D-Log M and HLG HDR for improved dynamic range and reduced banding, something that can be an issue when shooting skies. DJI&#39;s regular D-Log mode, which offers even more dynamic range, is not available on the Air 3, though. It also lacks a variable aperture found on the Mavic 3, so the optional ND filter kit (available in the Fly More combo) is desirable for sunny day flying to allow for lower shutter speeds and thus smoother video.</p><p> With the same 1/1.3-inch dual native ISO sensor and resolution as the Mini 3 Pro, image quality is similar — but there are some improvements on the Air 3. D-Log M offers better dynamic range, particularly in challenging contrasty shooting conditions. It also offers mildly better low-light capability, with less noise in shadows for nighttime cityscapes, for example.</p><p> The Air 3 delivers as good or even better video and photo quality than the larger sensor on the Air 2S, likely because the size difference is slight and the Air 3 has higher resolution. That said, it&#39;ll be interesting to see if DJI releases an Air 3S, possibly with a larger sensor.</p><h3> Wrap-up </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/7a0c5250-2a67-11ee-9ddd-0efb5000e860" style="height:1238px;width:2200px;" alt="DJI Air 3评测：高品质变焦增添新创意选择" data-uuid="ee93dd1c-1405-3dc3-a182-ad00005ac4ab"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Steve Dent for Engadget</div></figure><p> DJI has another winner with the Air 3 thanks to the dual cameras. By elevating the tele to the same importance as the main camera, it opens up new cinematic shooting options. It should prove popular with event and wedding pros who are willing to pay a few hundred dollars more than the Mini 3 Pro. In return, they get additional creative options, plus a more stable and secure camera drone.</p><p> Image quality might not be good enough for some pros when compared to the $2,200 Mavic 3 Pro, But at $1,100, it&#39;s considerably cheaper, more maneuverable, and offers the same features (including Waypoints) and level of obstacle protection. At the same time, it has a leg up on the Mini 3 Pro in terms of image quality thanks to the D-Log M option.</p><p> At $1,100 with the non-screen RC-N2 controller, the Air 3 is $330 more than the DJI Mini 3 Pro with the same controller. That goes up to $1,550 with the RC 2 Fly More kit, compared to $1,253 for the Mini 3 Pro in a similar kit. At those prices, its main competition is Autel&#39;s similarly priced 6K EVO Lite+ and the Mini 3 Pro itself. In any case, it&#39;s a great new option for drone buyers who might like the idea of two primary cameras and can&#39;t quite afford a Mavic 3 Pro.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/dji-air-3-review-a-high-quality-zoom-adds-new-creative-options-130020261.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/dji-air-3-review-a-high-quality-zoom-adds-new-creative-options-130020261.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ef204dc6-2b65-498d-8fda-56b368d1564a</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 25 Jul 2023 13:00:20 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690290656</ingested><modified> 2023-07-25T13:11:11+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Cameras & Photography]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1238" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/0f5566c0-2a41-11ee-bf93-99a976dfc24f" width="2200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1238" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/0f5566c0-2a41-11ee-bf93-99a976dfc24f" width="2200"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Steve Dent for Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[DJI Air 3 review: A high-quality zoom adds new creative options]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[DJI Air 3 review: A high-quality zoom adds new creative options]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best password managers for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> You might&#39;ve seen password managers in the news recently because of the <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://blog.lastpass.com/2022/12/notice-of-recent-security-incident/">breach affecting LastPass customers</a> . We need to trust that all of our logins, banking credentials and other sensitive information has been neatly locked away, only accessible by us when we need it. But most tech is fallible, and the benefits of unique, strong passwords across your online presence outweigh the risks. Password managers remain a great way to securely store all of the credentials you need on a regular basis. We tested out nine of the best password managers available now to help you choose the right one for your needs.</p><h2> How do password managers work?</h2><p> Think of password managers like virtual safe deposit boxes. They hold your valuables, in this case usually online credentials, in a section of the vault only accessible to you by security key or a master password. Most of these services have autofill features that make it convenient to log in to any site without needing to remember every password you have, and they keep your credit card information close for impulse purchases.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> But given that passwords are one of the <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/news/choosing-and-protecting-passwords">top ways to keep your online identity secure</a> , the real value of password managers is staying safe online. “It&#39;s just not possible without a password manager to have unique, long and hard-to-guess passwords,” Florian Schaub, an associate professor of information and of electrical engineering and computer science at the University of Michigan, said.</p><p> Common guidance states that secure passwords should be unique, with the longest number of characters allowed and uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers and special characters. This is the exact opposite of using one password everywhere, with minor variations depending on a site&#39;s requirements. Think of how many online accounts and sites you have credentials for — it&#39;s an impossible task to remember it all without somewhere to store passwords safely (no, a sticky note on your desk won&#39;t cut it). Password managers are more readily accessible and offer the benefit of filling in those long passwords for you.</p><h2> Are password managers safe?</h2><p> It seems counterintuitive to store all your sensitive information in one place. One hack could mean you lose it all to an attacker and struggle for months or even years to rebuild your online presence, not to mention you may have to cancel credit cards and other accounts. But most experts in the field agree that password managers are a generally secure and safe way to keep track of your personal data, and the benefits of strong, complex passwords outweigh the possible risks.</p><p> The mechanics of keeping those passwords safe differs slightly from provider to provider. Generally, you have a lengthy, complex “master password” that safeguards the rest of your information. In some cases, you might also get a “security key” to enter when you log in to new devices. This is a random string of letters, numbers and symbols that the company will send you at sign up. Only you know this key, and because it&#39;s stored locally on your device or printed out on paper, it&#39;s harder for hackers to find.</p><p> These multiple layers of security make it difficult for an attacker to get into your vault even if your password manager provider experiences a breach. But the company should also follow a few security basics. A “zero-knowledge” policy means that the company keeps none of your data on file, so in the event of an attack, there&#39;s nothing for hackers to find. Regular pentests and security audits are essential for keeping companies up to par on best practices, and other efforts like bug bounty programs or hosting on an open source website encourage constant vigilance for security flaws. Most password managers now also offer some level of encryption falling under the Advanced Encryption Standard (AES). AES 256-bit is the strongest, because there are the most number of possible combinations, but AES 128-bit or 192-bit are still good.</p><h2> Who are password managers for?</h2><p> Given their universal benefit, pretty much everyone could use a password manager. They&#39;re not just for the tech-savvy people or businesses anymore because so much sensitive information ends up online behind passwords, from our bank accounts to our Netflix watch history.</p><p> That&#39;s the other perk of password managers: safe password sharing. Families, friends or roommates can use them to safely access joint accounts. Texting a password to someone isn&#39;t secure, and you can help your family break the habit by starting to use one yourself, Lisa Plaggemier, executive director at National Cyber Security Alliance, said. Streaming is the obvious use case, but consider the shared bills, file storage and other sites you share access with the people around you as well.</p><h2> Are password managers worth it?</h2><p> You likely already use a password manager, even if you wouldn&#39;t think to call it that. Most phones and web browsers include a log of saved credentials on the device, like the “passwords” keychain in the settings of an iPhone. That means you&#39;ve probably seen the benefits of not having to memorize passwords or even type them out already.</p><p> While that&#39;s a great way in, the downfall of these built-in options are that they tend to be device specific. If you rely on an Apple password manager, for example, that works if you&#39;re totally in the Apple ecosystem — but you become limited once you get an Android tablet, Lujo Bauer, professor of electrical and computer engineering, and of computer science, at Carnegie Mellon University, said. If you use different devices for work and personal use and want a secure way to share passwords with others, or just don&#39;t want to be tied to one brand forever, a third-party password manager is usually worth it.</p><h2> How we tested</h2><p> We tested password managers by downloading the apps for each of the nine contenders on iPhone, Android, Safari, Chrome and Firefox. That helped us better understand what platforms each manager was available on, and see how support differs across operating systems and browsers.</p><p> As we got set up with each, we took note of how they iterated on the basic features of autofill and password generators. Nearly all password managers have these features, but some place limits on how much you can store while others give more control over creating easy-to-type yet complex passwords. From there, we looked at extra features like data-breach monitoring to understand which managers offered the most for your money.</p><p> Finally, we reviewed publicly available information about security specs for each. This includes LastPass, which more experts are shying away from recommending after the recent breach. For the sake of this review, we&#39;ve decided not to recommend LastPass at this time as fallout from the breach still comes to light (The company <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.wired.com/story/lastpass-engineer-breach-security-roundup/">disclosed a second incident earlier this year</a> where an unauthorized attack accessed the company&#39;s cloud storage, including sensitive data).</p><h2> Password managers we tested</h2><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:1Password;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=29d07367-7ffa-4e05-9a7f-c1dd19430630&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=1Password&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIyOWQwNzM2Ny03ZmZhLTRlMDUtOWE3Zi1jMWRkMTk0MzA2MzAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly8xcGFzc3dvcmQuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAedaFskljJO_nkmkybdzZwHxi54DX1OYVqiYqmgVWc-l&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2F1password.com%2F">1Password</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:LastPass;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4a567016-57fd-42ff-9497-6b31b5e02642&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=LastPass&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0YTU2NzAxNi01N2ZkLTQyZmYtOTQ5Ny02YjMxYjVlMDI2NDIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGFzdHBhc3MuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAARUxclm_QfTK0YNXnEiTcVaTUqctLb2EB9MVtaTUI3yG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lastpass.com%2F">LastPass</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://bitwarden.com/">Bitwarden</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dashlane;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=05a8faef-22e0-48ab-a365-0cc59778dc54&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dashlane&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwNWE4ZmFlZi0yMmUwLTQ4YWItYTM2NS0wY2M1OTc3OGRjNTQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGFzaGxhbmUuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATgyIRk0s8jpy1K1ohYYrEeJBH8EG2HW8Y3B-l7cs7a-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dashlane.com%2F">Dashlane</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Keeper;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f97fc99a-d04e-4e9c-b1e3-0bda0d13544b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Keeper&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmOTdmYzk5YS1kMDRlLTRlOWMtYjFlMy0wYmRhMGQxMzU0NGIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cua2VlcGVyc2VjdXJpdHkuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATagnPUDavwM7vNp3EMHBzMGgPTwHStvKr2uslYBnc_i&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.keepersecurity.com%2F">Keeper</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL25vcmRwYXNzLmNvbS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImE2NDlkOWQ2LTEwYzMtMzVhZi05NGMyLWRmZTkxOTI1MTU2YSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAXc3dvFt_FBTUl4eh8nwWwcOj_8uRtp4H_WvfMoCusWk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnordpass.com%2F">NordPass</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.enpass.io/">Enpass</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL215Lm5vcnRvbi5jb20vZXh0c3BhL3Bhc3N3b3JkbWFuYWdlciIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAWsN1q8IXBPU6hicsqTfsyaKAXp5TK7I6YbWqIudcDr6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fmy.norton.com%2Fextspa%2Fpasswordmanager">Norton password manager</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2xvZ21lb25jZS5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNjQ5ZDlkNi0xMGMzLTM1YWYtOTRjMi1kZmU5MTkyNTE1NmEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAR7AFD-nCuscZsY2B0g8D6XKA2e4UzrodET28_ZSzBBN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Flogmeonce.com%2F">LogMeOnce</a></p></li></ul><h2> Best password manager: 1Password</h2><p><core-commerce id="d02489763f8646d988255aa794bca9a9" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Many security experts trust <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:1Password;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=29d07367-7ffa-4e05-9a7f-c1dd19430630&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=1Password&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIyOWQwNzM2Ny03ZmZhLTRlMDUtOWE3Zi1jMWRkMTk0MzA2MzAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly8xcGFzc3dvcmQuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAedaFskljJO_nkmkybdzZwHxi54DX1OYVqiYqmgVWc-l&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2F1password.com%2F">1Password</a> with their private information and, after testing it out, it&#39;s clear why. The service includes industry standard encryption, a “secret key” that only you know on top of your master password, a zero-knowledge policy that means it keeps no data, and other security features like frequent audits and a bug bounty program.</p><p> Plus, 1Password apps have a pretty intuitive feel. A tutorial at download helps you import passwords from other managers onto 1Password so that you don&#39;t feel like you&#39;re starting over from scratch. It also clearly rates the strength of each password and has an “open and fill” option in the vault so that you can get into your desired site even more quickly. We also liked the option to scan a set up code to easily connect your account to your mobile devices without too much tedious typing.</p><p> At $3 per month, the individual subscription comes with unlimited passwords, items and one gigabyte of document storage for your vault. It also lets you share passwords, credit card information and other saved credentials. If you upgrade to the family plan for $5 each month, you&#39;ll get to invite up to five people (plus more for $1 each per month) to be a part of the vault.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 4</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> $3/month for Individual, $5/month for Families, $20/month for Teams Starter Pack, $8/month per user for Business</p></li><li><p> <strong>Compatibility:</strong> macOS, iOS, Windows, Android, Linux, Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Brave, Edge, Command Line</p></li></ul><h2> Best free password manager: Bitwarden</h2><p><core-commerce id="ff15057c13134c979a0870b47876b8d3" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://bitwarden.com/">Bitwarden&#39;s</a> free plan includes unlimited passwords on an unlimited number of devices, which is more than we&#39;ve seen from some of its competitors. There are drawbacks like you can only share vault items with one other user, but we think that&#39;s a fair tradeoff.</p><p> Bitwarden is based on open-source code, meaning anyone on GitHub can audit it, which is a good measure of security. On a personal level, it includes security audits of your information, like a data breach report, that can keep you in the know about when your passwords have been leaked and when it&#39;s time to change them. Plus, it&#39;s widely available across the platforms we tested, including Windows and iOS, with a level of customization, options to access your password vault and more.</p><p> Bitwarden may be the best free password manager, but it does have a paid version and we do think it&#39;s worth it. At $10 annually for individuals or $40 for families, you unlock encrypted file storage, emergency access, unlimited sharing and more. But the free version comes with the basics that can get anyone set up on password management easily.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 3</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free, $3/month per user for Teams Organization, $5/month per user for Enterprise Organization</p></li><li><p> <strong>Compatibility:</strong> macOS, iOS, Windows, Android, Linux, Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Brave, Edge, Vivaldi, Opera, Tor, DuckDuckGo for Mac, Command Line</p></li></ul><h2> Best password manager for cross-platform availability: NordPass</h2><p><core-commerce id="a86204c6b5004ba0a5c0cd3571100c6e" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Across password managers we tested, cross-platform availability was relatively similar. Most are widely available across web browsers and different operating systems, including our other top picks on this list. But we wanted to give a nod to <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL25vcmRwYXNzLmNvbS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImE2NDlkOWQ2LTEwYzMtMzVhZi05NGMyLWRmZTkxOTI1MTU2YSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAXc3dvFt_FBTUl4eh8nwWwcOj_8uRtp4H_WvfMoCusWk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fnordpass.com%2F">NordPass</a> here because of how easy the service makes it to access your vault from any platform.</p><p> NordPass has a free option with unlimited passwords and syncs across devices. A $2-per-month premium plan keeps you logged in when switching devices, comes with security notifications and allows for item sharing. A family subscription comes with six premium accounts and only costs $4 per month. This makes it a pretty good budget option as well. Besides the pairing code to connect accounts, NordPass is a pretty standard password manager. Scanning a code gets me from my laptop to mobile device to work computer super easily. If you&#39;re constantly switching devices and those extra few seconds save your sanity, it&#39;s worth considering.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 3</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free, $2/per month for Premium, $4/month for Family</p></li><li><p> <strong>Compatibility:</strong> macOS, iOS, Windows, Android, Linux, Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Opera, Edge</p></li></ul><h2> Best password manager for shared access: Dashlane</h2><p><core-commerce id="e512d97e6be44fba96f1362969567b59" data-type="product-list"></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Dashlane;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=05a8faef-22e0-48ab-a365-0cc59778dc54&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Dashlane&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwNWE4ZmFlZi0yMmUwLTQ4YWItYTM2NS0wY2M1OTc3OGRjNTQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGFzaGxhbmUuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTY0OWQ5ZDYtMTBjMy0zNWFmLTk0YzItZGZlOTE5MjUxNTZhIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATgyIRk0s8jpy1K1ohYYrEeJBH8EG2HW8Y3B-l7cs7a-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dashlane.com%2F">Dashlane</a> has four subscription options: A free user gets access to one device with unlimited passwords; an advanced user pays $3 per month to get upgraded to unlimited devices and dark web monitoring; for $5 per month, a premium user also gets VPN access and an $7.49-per-month family plan includes access for up to 10 people.</p><p> It met all the criteria we looked for, but with a clear emphasis on sharing credentials. Dashlane highlights “secure sharing” starting at its free level, which is a feature that some competitors keep behind a paywall. Access for up to 10 members in a family plan is one of the bigger plans we&#39;ve seen as well. While we were testing it, password sharing seemed front of mind with a tab dedicated to it in Dashlane&#39;s browser extension. Arguably the biggest caveat here, though, is lack of Linux support.</p><ul><li><p> <strong>Number of tiers:</strong> 4</p></li><li><p> <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free, $3/month for Advanced, $5/month for Premium, $7/month for Friends and Family</p></li><li><p> <strong>Compatibility:</strong> macOS, iOS, Android, Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Brave, Edge, Opera</p></li></ul><h2> FAQs</h2><h3> Why use a password manager?</h3><p> Using a password manager can enhance your online security. They store all of your complex passwords and autofill them as needed, so that you can have unique, strong passwords across the web without remembering each of them yourself. In many cases, unique passwords are your first defense against attack, and a reliable manager makes it easier to keep track of them all.</p><h3> How secure are password managers?</h3><p> Password managers are a secure way to store your credentials. Experts in the field generally agree that the benefits of accessibility when storing complex passwords outweigh the possibility of attack, like what happened with LastPass. But with any service, it can vary from provider to provider. You should look out for zero-knowledge policies, regular security audits, pentests, bug bounty programs and encryption when choosing the right password manager for you.</p><h3> What if I forget my master password?</h3><p> Forgetting a master password won&#39;t necessarily lock you out for good, but the recovery process varies from provider to provider. Some services give you a “security key” at sign up to enter when you log into new devices. It can also be used to securely recover your account because it&#39;s a random string of keys stored locally that only you have access to. Other services, however, have no way to recover your vault. So creating a master password that you won&#39;t forget is important.</p><h3> How can I make a good master password?</h3><p> A good master password should be unique, with the longest number of characters allowed and uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers and special characters. Experts often recommended thinking of it like a “passphrase” instead of a “password” to make it easier to remember. For example, you can take a sentence like “My name is Bob Smith” and change it to “Myn@m3isB0b5m!th” to turn it into a secure master password that you won&#39;t forget.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-password-manager-134639599.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-password-manager-134639599.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a649d9d6-10c3-35af-94c2-dfe91925156a</guid><dc:creator>凯蒂·马龙</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder